#: ../../skills.rst:2
msgid "研究技能"
msgstr "Research Skills"

#: ../../skills.rst:4
msgid "AgentSociety 2 包含一组 LLM 原生的研究技能，用于自动化科学研究工作流。"
msgstr ""
"AgentSociety 2 includes a set of LLM-native research skills for "
"automating scientific research workflows."

#: ../../skills.rst:7
msgid "概述"
msgstr "Overview"

#: ../../skills.rst:9
msgid "研究技能模块提供以下功能："
msgstr "The research skills module provides the following capabilities:"

#: ../../skills.rst:11
msgid "**文献检索**: 搜索和管理学术论文"
msgstr "**Literature Search**: Search and manage academic papers"

#: ../../skills.rst:12
msgid "**假设生成**: 从研究问题生成可测试的假设"
msgstr ""
"**Hypothesis Generation**: Generate testable hypotheses from research "
"questions"

#: ../../skills.rst:13
msgid "**实验设计**: 设计完整的实验配置"
msgstr "**Experiment Design**: Design complete experiment configurations"

#: ../../skills.rst:14
msgid "**论文撰写**: 通过 paper-orchestrator skill 套件（重写中）生成 Nature 风格学术论文 PDF"
msgstr ""
"**Paper writing**: Generate Nature-style academic paper PDF through the paper-"
"orchestrator skill suite (under rewriting)"

#: ../../skills.rst:15
msgid "**数据分析**: 分析实验数据并生成报告"
msgstr "**Data Analysis**: Analyze experiment data and generate reports"

#: ../../skills.rst:17
msgid ""
"当前 Python 包内公开的 research skills 模块为 "
"``agentsociety2.skills.literature``、``agentsociety2.skills.hypothesis``、 "
"``agentsociety2.skills.experiment``、``agentsociety2.skills.analysis``、 "
"``agentsociety2.skills.paper``。"
msgstr ""
"The research skill modules publicly exposed in the current Python package"
" are ``agentsociety2.skills.literature``, "
"``agentsociety2.skills.hypothesis``, ``agentsociety2.skills.experiment``,"
" ``agentsociety2.skills.analysis``, and ``agentsociety2.skills.paper``."

#: ../../skills.rst:23
msgid "Claude Code Skills"
msgstr "Claude Code Skills"

#: ../../skills.rst:25
msgid "研究工作流主要通过 Claude Code 的“skills-first”方式提供："
msgstr ""
"Research workflows are primarily provided through Claude Code’s “skills-"
"first” approach:"

#: ../../skills.rst:27
msgid "AgentSociety 内置研究 skills：随 VSCode 插件打包，可在插件树视图中浏览（只读）。"
msgstr ""
"AgentSociety built-in research skills: packaged with the VSCode plugin "
"and can be browsed in the plugin tree view (read-only)."

#: ../../skills.rst:28
msgid "Agent(Person) 扩展 skills：由后端 `/api/v1/agent-skills/*` 管理，支持扫描/导入/热重载。"
msgstr ""
"Agent (Person) extended skills: managed by the backend `/api/v1/agent-"
"skills/*`, supporting scanning/import/hot reload."

#: ../../skills.rst:30
msgid "**agentsociety-literature-search** - 文献检索"
msgstr "**agentsociety-literature-search** - Literature search"

#: ../../skills.rst:31
msgid "**agentsociety-hypothesis** - 假设管理（add, get, list, delete）"
msgstr ""
"**agentsociety-hypothesis** - Assumption management (add, get, list, "
"delete)"

#: ../../skills.rst:32
msgid "**agentsociety-experiment-config** - 实验配置生成与验证"
msgstr ""
"**agentsociety-experiment-config** - Experimental configuration "
"generation and verification"

#: ../../skills.rst:33
msgid "**agentsociety-run-experiment** - 实验执行与监控"
msgstr "**agentsociety-run-experiment** - Experiment execution and monitoring"

#: ../../skills.rst:34
msgid "**agentsociety-analysis** - 数据分析与跨实验综合"
msgstr "**agentsociety-analysis** - Data analysis and cross-experimental synthesis"

#: ../../skills.rst:35
msgid "**agentsociety-create-agent** - 自定义 Agent 生成与校验"
msgstr "**agentsociety-create-agent** - Custom Agent generation and verification"

#: ../../skills.rst:36
msgid "**agentsociety-paper-orchestrator** - Nature/Science 级论文生成（6-skill 状态机）"
msgstr ""
"**agentsociety-paper-orchestrator** - Nature/Science level paper "
"generation (6-skill state machine)"

#: ../../skills.rst:40
msgid ""
"本页中的 ``.agentsociety/bin/ags.py`` 命令面向**已初始化的工作区**。 如果当前目录尚未生成 "
"``.agentsociety/``，请先执行："
msgstr ""
"The ``.agentsociety/bin/ags.py`` commands shown on this page are intended"
" for an **initialized workspace**. If the current directory does not yet "
"contain ``.agentsociety/``, run the following first:"

#: ../../skills.rst:47
msgid "等价入口是 ``python -m agentsociety2.society.workspace init --target-dir .``。"
msgstr ""
"An equivalent entry point is ``python -m agentsociety2.society.workspace "
"init --target-dir .``."

#: ../../skills.rst:50
msgid "create-agent 技能"
msgstr "create-agent skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:52
msgid ""
"``agentsociety-create-agent`` 用于创建或修订工作区里的自定义 Agent 类型。它不是 PersonAgent "
"内置认知技能，而是研究工作流中的开发辅助 skill：当实验需要一个当前不存在的 Agent class 时，通常由 "
"``agentsociety-experiment-config`` 分支调用。"
msgstr ""
"``agentsociety-create-agent`` Used to create or revise custom Agent types"
" in the workspace. It is not a built-in cognitive skill of PersonAgent, "
"but a development auxiliary skill in the research workflow: when the "
"experiment requires an Agent class that does not currently exist, it is "
"usually called by the ``agentsociety-experiment-config`` branch."

#: ../../skills.rst:54
msgid "**文件位置与扫描规则**:"
msgstr "**File location and scan rules**:"

#: ../../skills.rst:56
msgid ""
"新 Agent 模块应放在 ``custom/agents/`` 下，例如 "
"``custom/agents/research/lab_agent.py``。"
msgstr ""
"New Agent modules should be placed under ``custom/agents/``, for example "
"``custom/agents/research/lab_agent.py``."

#: ../../skills.rst:57
msgid "扫描器会读取该目录下的 ``*.py``，但跳过路径片段包含 ``examples/`` 的文件。"
msgstr ""
"The scanner reads ``*.py`` in this directory, but skips files whose path "
"fragment contains ``examples/``."

#: ../../skills.rst:58
msgid "推荐一个文件一个主要 Agent class；一个文件中存在多个 ``AgentBase`` 子类时，扫描器也能发现。"
msgstr ""
"It is recommended to have one main Agent class per file; when there are "
"multiple ``AgentBase`` subclasses in a file, the scanner can also find "
"it."

#: ../../skills.rst:60
msgid "**基类选择**:"
msgstr "**Base class selection**:"

#: ../../skills.rst:66
msgid "基类"
msgstr "Base class"

#: ../../skills.rst:67
msgid "适用场景"
msgstr "Applicable scenarios"

#: ../../skills.rst:68
msgid "``AgentBase``"
msgstr "``AgentBase``"

#: ../../skills.rst:69
msgid "简单实验、博弈/基准场景，开发者自行管理状态。"
msgstr ""
"Simple experiments, games/benchmark scenarios, developers manage the "
"status by themselves."

#: ../../skills.rst:70
msgid "``PersonAgent``"
msgstr "``PersonAgent``"

#: ../../skills.rst:71
msgid "需要 skills-first 工具循环、workspace、checkpoint/WAL 与持久化记忆。"
msgstr ""
"Requires skills-first tool loops, workspace, checkpoint/WAL and "
"persistent memory."

#: ../../skills.rst:73
msgid "**本地校验**:"
msgstr "**Local validation**:"

#: ../../skills.rst:83
msgid ""
"校验器会检查：目标文件为 Python 文件、至少有一个直接继承 ``AgentBase`` 或 ``PersonAgent`` "
"的类、``ask`` / ``step`` / ``dump`` / ``load`` 均为 ``async "
"def``、模块可动态导入、目标类不是 abstract class。创建完成后，在 VS Code 扩展中执行 **Scan Custom "
"Modules** 让后端重新发现模块。"
msgstr ""
"The validator will check: the target file is a Python file, there is at "
"least one class that directly inherits ``AgentBase`` or ``PersonAgent``, "
"``ask`` / ``step`` / ``dump`` / ``load`` are all ``async def``, the "
"module can be imported dynamically, and the target class is not abstract "
"class. After creation, execute **Scan Custom Modules** in the VS Code "
"extension to let the backend rediscover the module."

#: ../../skills.rst:87
msgid "实验工作流"
msgstr "Experiment workflow"

#: ../../skills.rst:89
msgid "研究 pipeline 的主干是："
msgstr "The backbone of the research pipeline is:"

#: ../../skills.rst:91
msgid ""
"``literature-search → hypothesis → experiment-config → run-experiment → "
"analysis → paper-orchestrator``"
msgstr ""
"``literature-search → hypothesis → experiment-config → run-experiment → "
"analysis → paper-orchestrator``"

#: ../../skills.rst:93
msgid "实验相关的两个核心 skill 是："
msgstr "The two core skills related to experiments are:"

#: ../../skills.rst:99
msgid "Skill"
msgstr "Skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:100
msgid "主要输入"
msgstr "Main input"

#: ../../skills.rst:101
msgid "主要输出"
msgstr "Main output"

#: ../../skills.rst:102
msgid "``agentsociety-experiment-config``"
msgstr "``agentsociety-experiment-config``"

#: ../../skills.rst:103
msgid "``SIM_SETTINGS.json``、已有 Agent/Env/Dataset 信息"
msgstr "``SIM_SETTINGS.json``, existing Agent/Env/Dataset information"

#: ../../skills.rst:104
msgid "``init_config.json``、``steps.yaml``、``config_params.py``"
msgstr "``init_config.json``、``steps.yaml``、``config_params.py``"

#: ../../skills.rst:105
msgid "``agentsociety-run-experiment``"
msgstr "``agentsociety-run-experiment``"

#: ../../skills.rst:106
msgid "``init_config.json`` + ``steps.yaml``"
msgstr "``init_config.json`` + ``steps.yaml``"

#: ../../skills.rst:107
msgid "``run/sqlite.db``、日志、artifacts、``pid.json``"
msgstr "``run/sqlite.db``, logs, artifacts, ``pid.json``"

#: ../../skills.rst:109 ../../skills.rst:123
msgid "推荐流程："
msgstr "Recommended process:"

#: ../../skills.rst:111
msgid "先确认工作区中已经具备 ``init_config.json``、``steps.yaml`` 与所需模块信息。"
msgstr ""
"First confirm that the workspace already contains ``init_config.json``, "
"``steps.yaml``, and the required module information."

#: ../../skills.rst:112
msgid "在 ``experiment-config`` 阶段先扫描模块；如果缺少 Agent 或 Env，先补充对应自定义模块，再重新扫描。"
msgstr ""
"During the ``experiment-config`` stage, scan modules first. If an Agent "
"or environment module is missing, add the corresponding custom module and"
" then scan again."

#: ../../skills.rst:113
msgid "运行 ``experiment-config check`` 或等价校验，确认配置和步骤文件可用。"
msgstr ""
"Run ``experiment-config check`` or equivalent verification to confirm "
"that the configuration and step files are available."

#: ../../skills.rst:114
msgid "启动实验时使用 ``run-experiment``；后台执行必须指定日志文件，避免丢失 verbose 输出。"
msgstr ""
"Use ``run-experiment`` when starting the experiment; a log file must be "
"specified for background execution to avoid losing verbose output."

#: ../../skills.rst:115
msgid "实验完成后检查 ``run/sqlite.db``、日志与 artifacts，再进入分析阶段。"
msgstr ""
"After the experiment is completed, check ``run/sqlite.db``, logs, and "
"artifacts before entering the analysis phase."

#: ../../skills.rst:119
msgid "分析工作流"
msgstr "Analysis workflow"

#: ../../skills.rst:121
msgid ""
"``agentsociety-analysis`` 面向已完成实验的数据解释、图表和报告生成。它要求目标 run 目录中已经存在 "
"``sqlite.db``；如果数据库不存在，应回到 ``run-experiment`` 或配置修复阶段。"
msgstr ""
"``agentsociety-analysis`` Data interpretation, graphs and report "
"generation for completed experiments. It requires that ``sqlite.db`` "
"already exists in the target run directory; if the database does not "
"exist, you should fall back to ``run-experiment`` or the configuration "
"repair phase."

#: ../../skills.rst:125
msgid "**加载上下文**：读取 hypothesis、experiment config、steps 和 run 元数据。"
msgstr "**Load context**: Read hypothesis, experiment config, steps, and run metadata."

#: ../../skills.rst:126
msgid "**确认问题**：明确本次分析是验证假设、解释异常、比较组间差异，还是生成报告。"
msgstr ""
"**Clarify the question**: Clarify whether this analysis is to test hypotheses, explain "
"anomalies, compare differences between groups, or generate a report."

#: ../../skills.rst:127
msgid "**探索数据**：列出 SQLite 表，查看 schema、行数、关键字段和缺失情况。"
msgstr ""
"**Explore data**: List the SQLite tables and view the schema, number of rows, key "
"fields, and missing values."

#: ../../skills.rst:128
msgid "**提出发现**：先给出可检验发现，再决定需要哪些图表。"
msgstr ""
"**Propose findings**: Present testable findings first, then decide which charts "
"are needed."

#: ../../skills.rst:129
msgid "**生成图表**：单实验默认最多 5 张图；每张图在报告中必须有一句说明。"
msgstr ""
"**Generate charts**: A single experiment can have up to 5 charts by default; each "
"chart must have a corresponding explanation in the report."

#: ../../skills.rst:130
#, python-brace-format
msgid "**写报告**：单实验输出到 ``presentation/hypothesis_{id}/``，跨实验综合输出到 ``synthesis/``。"
msgstr ""
"**Write report**: Single-experiment output goes to ``presentation/hypothesis_{id}/``, "
"and cross-experiment synthesis output goes to ``synthesis/``."

#: ../../skills.rst:132
msgid "常用命令："
msgstr "Commonly used commands:"

#: ../../skills.rst:143
msgid "文献检索服务"
msgstr "Literature search service"

#: ../../skills.rst:145
msgid ""
"``agentsociety-literature-search`` 通过统一的远程检索服务收集学术文献，并把结果保存到工作区 "
"``papers/`` "
"目录。默认检索所有已配置数据源：``local``、``arxiv``、``crossref``、``openalex``。"
msgstr ""
"``agentsociety-literature-search`` Collect academic literature through a "
"unified remote search service and save the results to the workspace "
"``papers/`` directory. All configured data sources are retrieved by "
"default: ``local``, ``arxiv``, ``crossref``, ``openalex``."

#: ../../skills.rst:147
msgid "配置项："
msgstr "Configuration:"

#: ../../skills.rst:154
msgid "搜索命令示例："
msgstr "Search command example:"

#: ../../skills.rst:161
msgid "输出约定："
msgstr "Output convention:"

#: ../../skills.rst:163
msgid ""
"``papers/literature_index.json`` 是稳定索引，记录标题、作者、年份、来源、query、分数和本地 "
"``file_path``。"
msgstr ""
"``papers/literature_index.json`` is a stable index, recording title, "
"author, year, source, query, score and local ``file_path``."

#: ../../skills.rst:164
msgid ""
"每篇文献保存为 ``papers/<title>_<timestamp>.md``，这是后续 hypothesis、analysis 和 "
"paper 技能引用的主要本地笔记。"
msgstr ""
"Each document is saved as ``papers/<title>_<timestamp>.md``, which is the"
" main local note cited in subsequent hypothesis, analysis and paper "
"skills."

#: ../../skills.rst:165
msgid ""
"原文 PDF 如需下载，应放在 ``papers/full_texts/``，并记录到 "
"``extra_fields.full_text.file_path``；不要把索引中的 ``file_path`` 从 Markdown "
"笔记替换成 PDF。"
msgstr ""
"If the original PDF is to be downloaded, it should be placed in "
"``papers/full_texts/`` and recorded in "
"``extra_fields.full_text.file_path``; do not replace ``file_path`` in the"
" index from Markdown notes to PDF."

#: ../../skills.rst:166
msgid "文献检索不会自动绕过出版商权限。PDF 下载只处理开放获取或用户授权的文件；没有开放 PDF 时，可以补充本地 Markdown 笔记并记录来源。"
msgstr ""
"Literature search does not bypass publisher access controls. PDF "
"downloads only process open-access or user-authorized files. If no open "
"PDF is available, local Markdown notes may be added together with the "
"recorded source."

#: ../../skills.rst:169
msgid "Python API"
msgstr "Python API"

#: ../../skills.rst:171
msgid "研究技能也可以通过 Python API 直接调用。"
msgstr "Research skills can also be called directly through the Python API."

#: ../../skills.rst:174
msgid "文献技能 (literature)"
msgstr "Literature Skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:176
msgid ""
"文献技能默认使用已经配置好的 ``LITERATURE_SEARCH_API_URL`` 和 "
"``LITERATURE_SEARCH_API_KEY`` 调用统一检索服务。推荐优先使用 "
"``search_literature_and_save``，而不是直接调用底层 ``search_literature``： "
"前者会把检索结果落到工作区中，确保后续 Agent、Claude Code 和论文写作技能 都能通过本地文件继续引用这些文献。"
msgstr ""
"By default, the literature skill uses the configured "
"``LITERATURE_SEARCH_API_URL`` and ``LITERATURE_SEARCH_API_KEY`` to call "
"the unified search service. It is recommended to use "
"``search_literature_and_save`` instead of calling the underlying "
"``search_literature`` directly: the former will drop the search results "
"into the workspace, ensuring that subsequent Agent, Claude Code and paper"
" writing skills can continue to reference these documents through local "
"files."

#: ../../skills.rst:207
msgid "**保存结果**:"
msgstr "**Save results**:"

#: ../../skills.rst:209
msgid ""
"每篇检索结果都会保存为 ``papers/<title>_<timestamp>.md``。 这个 Markdown "
"文件是稳定的本地文献笔记，包含标题、检索词、年份、期刊、 DOI/URL、摘要、作者和相关内容片段。"
msgstr ""
"Each search result will be saved as ``papers/<title>_<timestamp>.md``. "
"This Markdown file is a stable local literature note that contains title,"
" search terms, year, journal, DOI/URL, abstract, author, and related "
"content fragments."

#: ../../skills.rst:212
msgid ""
"``papers/literature_index.json`` 会同步更新。索引中的 ``file_path`` 指向本地 Markdown "
"文献笔记，因此插件中的 ``@引用`` 可以复制为 ``@papers/<title>_<timestamp>.md``，供 Claude "
"Code 或 Agent 读取。"
msgstr ""
"``papers/literature_index.json`` will be updated simultaneously. "
"``file_path`` in the index points to the local Markdown literature note, so"
" the ``@cite`` button in the plug-in can be copied as "
"``@papers/<title>_<timestamp>.md`` for Claude Code or Agent to read."

#: ../../skills.rst:215
msgid "重复运行检索时会生成新的本地文献笔记，并追加到索引中，便于保留不同检索轮次的上下文。"
msgstr ""
"When a search is run repeatedly, new local literature notes are generated"
" and appended to the index, allowing context to be retained across "
"different search rounds."

#: ../../skills.rst:217
msgid "**原文下载（由 Claude/Agent 按需执行）**:"
msgstr "**Full-text download (on demand by Claude/Agent)**:"

#: ../../skills.rst:219
msgid ""
"文献技能不会在 Python API 中硬编码下载策略。检索结果会尽量保留 "
"``doi``、``url``、``pdf_url``、``full_text_url``、``download_url``、 "
"``open_access``、``best_oa_location`` 等元信息；Claude Code 或 Agent "
"可以基于这些线索按需下载开放获取原文。"
msgstr ""
"The literature skill does not hardcode download policies in the Python API."
" The search results will try to retain meta-information such as ``doi``, "
"``url``, ``pdf_url``, ``full_text_url``, ``download_url``, "
"``open_access``, ``best_oa_location``; Claude Code or Agent can download "
"the open access original text on demand based on these clues."

#: ../../skills.rst:224
msgid "建议的下载约定："
msgstr "Recommended download conventions:"

#: ../../skills.rst:226
msgid "原文 PDF 放在 ``papers/full_texts/*.pdf``。"
msgstr "The original PDF is located at ``papers/full_texts/*.pdf``."

#: ../../skills.rst:227
msgid ""
"优先使用 API 返回的 PDF 直链；arXiv 论文可从 ``/abs/<id>`` 转为 "
"``https://arxiv.org/pdf/<id>.pdf``。"
msgstr ""
"Priority is given to PDF direct links returned by the API; arXiv papers "
"can be converted from ``/abs/<id>`` to "
"``https://arxiv.org/pdf/<id>.pdf``."

#: ../../skills.rst:229
msgid "DOI 仅作为落地页线索，不保证能直接得到 PDF；如果需要下载，应确认最终响应确实是 PDF。"
msgstr ""
"The DOI is only used as a landing page clue, and there is no guarantee "
"that the PDF will be obtained directly; if you need to download it, you "
"should confirm that the final response is indeed a PDF."

#: ../../skills.rst:230
msgid "下载完成后，可在对应索引条目的 ``extra_fields[\"full_text\"]`` 中记录:"
msgstr ""
"After the download is completed, it can be recorded in "
"``extra_fields[\"full_text\"]`` of the corresponding index entry:"

#: ../../skills.rst:240
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"如果没有找到开放原文，也可以记录 ``{\"status\": \"no_candidate\"}`` 或 ``{\"status\": "
"\"failed\", \"reason\": \"...\"}``，便于插件页面显示状态。"
msgstr ""
"If the open original text is not found, you can also record "
"``{\"status\": \"no_candidate\"}`` or ``{\"status\": \"failed\", "
"\"reason\": \"...\"}`` to facilitate the plug-in page to display the "
"status."

#: ../../skills.rst:245
msgid ""
"许多 CrossRef/OpenAlex 结果只提供 DOI 或落地页，不一定有开放 PDF。 Claude/Agent "
"不应绕过出版商权限，也不应把 HTML 落地页当作 PDF 保存。"
msgstr ""
"Many CrossRef/OpenAlex results only offer a DOI or landing page, not "
"necessarily an open PDF. Claude/Agent should not bypass publisher "
"permissions or save HTML landing pages as PDFs."

#: ../../skills.rst:248
msgid ""
"**数据源**: - ``local``: RAGFlow 本地知识库 - ``arxiv``: arXiv 预印本平台 - "
"``crossref``: CrossRef DOI 元数据库 - ``openalex``: OpenAlex 学术图谱 (2.5亿+ 论文)"
msgstr ""
"**Data sources**: - ``local``: RAGFlow local knowledge base - ``arxiv``: arXiv "
"preprint platform - ``crossref``: CrossRef DOI metadata repository - "
"``openalex``: OpenAlex scholarly graph (250 million+ papers)"

#: ../../skills.rst:254
msgid "**配置**: 需要在 ``.env`` 文件中配置 API:"
msgstr "**Configuration**: API needs to be configured in the ``.env`` file:"

#: ../../skills.rst:263
msgid "假设技能 (hypothesis)"
msgstr "Hypothesis Skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:279
msgid "实验技能 (experiment)"
msgstr "Experiment Skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:300
msgid "分析技能 (analysis)"
msgstr "Analysis Skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:318
msgid ""
"跨实验对比不再使用独立综合 skill，而是作为 ``agentsociety-analysis`` 的 Stage 5 在 Claude "
"Code 中完成。"
msgstr ""
"The cross-experiment comparison no longer uses independent comprehensive "
"skills, but is completed in Claude Code as Stage 5 of ``agentsociety-"
"analysis``."

#: ../../skills.rst:322
msgid "论文技能 (paper)"
msgstr "Paper Skill"

#: ../../skills.rst:324
msgid ""
"论文生成由 6 个 plugin skill 组成的状态机驱动，通过 ``paper-orchestrator`` "
"作为唯一入口点调度。Python 包 ``agentsociety2.skills.paper`` 提供非 LLM 逻辑（状态管理、适配器、 "
"LaTeX 编译）。"
msgstr ""
"Paper generation is driven by a state machine composed of 6 plugin skills, "
"scheduled through ``paper-orchestrator`` as the sole entry point. "
"The Python package ``agentsociety2.skills.paper`` provides non-LLM logic "
"(state management, adapters, LaTeX compilation)."

#: ../../skills.rst:329
msgid "**Skill 套件：**"
msgstr "**Skill suite:**"

#: ../../skills.rst:331
msgid ""
"``agentsociety-paper-orchestrator`` — 状态机内核，读取 ``paper_state.yaml``，调度 "
"Task subagent，持久化产出"
msgstr ""
"``agentsociety-paper-orchestrator`` — State machine kernel, read "
"``paper_state.yaml``, schedule Task subagent, persist output"

#: ../../skills.rst:333
msgid "``agentsociety-paper-adapter`` — workspace → ResearchPack 标准化"
msgstr "``agentsociety-paper-adapter`` — workspace → ResearchPack Standardization"

#: ../../skills.rst:334
msgid "``agentsociety-paper-framing`` — storyline_map 生成（问题、角度、贡献类型）"
msgstr ""
"``agentsociety-paper-framing`` — storyline_map generation (issue, angle, "
"contribution type)"

#: ../../skills.rst:335
msgid "``agentsociety-paper-evidence-expansion`` — 证据缺口审计与补全"
msgstr ""
"``agentsociety-paper-evidence-expansion`` — Audit and completion of "
"evidence gaps"

#: ../../skills.rst:336
msgid ""
"``agentsociety-paper-architecture`` — claim tree + figure-argument map + "
"章节大纲 + manuscript 草稿"
msgstr ""
"``agentsociety-paper-architecture`` — claim tree + figure-argument map + "
"chapter outline + manuscript draft"

#: ../../skills.rst:338
msgid ""
"``agentsociety-paper-skeptical-review`` — 3 审稿人评审轮次（significance-"
"calibrator / precision-editor / evidence-skeptic）"
msgstr ""
"``agentsociety-paper-skeptical-review`` — 3 reviewer review rounds "
"(significance-calibrator / precision-editor / evidence-skeptic)"

#: ../../skills.rst:341
msgid "**状态机阶段：**"
msgstr "**State machine stages:**"

#: ../../skills.rst:343
msgid ""
"``intake → framing → evidence-audit → expansion-plan → manuscript-build →"
" skeptical-review → revision-router → release-gate``"
msgstr ""
"``intake → framing → evidence-audit → expansion-plan → manuscript-build →"
" skeptical-review → revision-router → release-gate``"

#: ../../skills.rst:346
msgid "**持久化布局：**"
msgstr "**Persistence layout:**"

#: ../../skills.rst:348
msgid "所有论文状态持久化在 ``<workspace>/paper/`` 下："
msgstr "The status of all papers is persisted under ``<workspace>/paper/``:"

#: ../../skills.rst:350
msgid "``paper_meta.yaml`` — 标题、作者、机构"
msgstr "``paper_meta.yaml`` — Title, Author, Institution"

#: ../../skills.rst:351
msgid ""
"``state/`` — "
"``paper_state.yaml``、``research_pack.json``、``human_gates.yaml``"
msgstr ""
"``state/`` — "
"``paper_state.yaml``、``research_pack.json``、``human_gates.yaml``"

#: ../../skills.rst:352
msgid ""
"``artifacts/`` — ``storyline_map.json``、``claim_ledger.json``、 "
"``evidence_backlog.json``、``figure_argument_map.json``、 "
"``manuscript/``（``abstract.md``、``main.md``、``results/``、``discussion.md``）"
msgstr ""
"``artifacts/`` — ``storyline_map.json``、``claim_ledger.json``、 "
"``evidence_backlog.json``、``figure_argument_map.json``、 "
"``manuscript/``（``abstract.md``、``main.md``、``results/``、``discussion.md``）"

#: ../../skills.rst:355
msgid "``reviews/`` — ``review_round_NNN.yaml``"
msgstr "``reviews/`` — ``review_round_NNN.yaml``"

#: ../../skills.rst:356
msgid "``runs/<TS>/compose/out/paper.pdf`` — 最终交付物"
msgstr "``runs/<TS>/compose/out/paper.pdf`` — Final deliverable"

#: ../../skills.rst:358
msgid "**CLI 入口：**"
msgstr "**CLI entry point:**"

#: ../../skills.rst:360
msgid "``$PYTHON_PATH .agentsociety/bin/ags.py paper-orchestrator <subcommand>``"
msgstr "``$PYTHON_PATH .agentsociety/bin/ags.py paper-orchestrator <subcommand>``"

#: ../../skills.rst:362
msgid ""
"子命令：init-meta, intake, build-pack, framing, evidence, architecture, "
"review, compile, run-loop, status。别名 ``paper``、``generate-paper``、 "
"``generate_paper`` 均路由至此。执行前提同上：需要位于已初始化工作区内， 且 "
"``.agentsociety/bin/ags.py`` 已可用。"
msgstr ""
"Subcommands: init-meta, intake, build-pack, framing, evidence, "
"architecture, review, compile, run-loop, status. The aliases ``paper``, "
"``generate-paper``, and ``generate_paper`` all route here. The same "
"prerequisites apply: the command must run inside an initialized "
"workspace, and ``.agentsociety/bin/ags.py`` must already be available."

